By Oluwatope Lawanson Ikeja – An Ikeja Chief Magistrate’s Court  on Thursday ordered the remand of a 28-year-old man, Dayo Olawale, who allegedly sexually assaulted a 20-year-old lady. Chief Magistrate Olufunke Sule-Amzat, who did not take the plea of
the defendant, ordered that he  should be kept at the Kirikiri Prisons,
Lagos. The chief magistrate also directed that the case file should be sent to the state director of public prosecutions for advice. She adjourned the case until July 8 for mention. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that Olawale, who resides at
Eruwen, Ikorodu, Lagos State, is facing a two-count charge of
conspiracy and sexual assault. Earlier, the prosecutor, ASP Benson Emuerhi, said that the defendant
committed the offences on April 22, at 6.00p.m. at No. 66, Asiwaju
Crescent Elepe Road, Ikorodu, Lagos State. Emuerhi alleged that the defendant conspired with others still at large and sexually assaulted the 20-year-old. “The defendant sexually assaulted the woman by forcefully having sexual intercourse with her,” he said. He said that the victim  reported the case  at the Elepe Police
Division, adding that the case was later transferred to the Gender
Section of the Ikeja Police Command. The prosecutor said that the offences contravened Sections 261 and 411 of the Criminal Laws of Lagos State 2015.